<raw><![CDATA[    Investing.com – The pound extended losses against the U.S. dollar on Thursday, falling to an eight-day low amid growing uncertainty over the prospect of fresh stimulus plans by the Federal Reserve ahead of a speech by the central bank’s head on Friday.GBP/USD hit 1.6296 during U.S. morning trade, the pair’s lowest since August 15; the pair subsequently consolidated at 1.6294, shedding 0.47%.Cable was likely to find support at 1.6165, the low of August 12 and resistance at 1.6396, the days high.Ahead of Friday’s speech by Fed chair Ben Bernanke, concerns mounted that he would not outline plans for a third round of quantitative easing to support the faltering U.S. economy, but would instead stress that the central bank remained ready to act if necessary.Earlier Thursday, U.S. Labor Department said the number of people who filed for unemployment assistance in the U.S. last week unexpectedly rose by 5,000 to a seasonally adjusted 417,000, confounding expectations for a decline to 405,000. The previous week’s figure was revised up to 412,000 from 408,000. Meanwhile, the pound was almost unchanged against the euro, with EUR/GBP inching up 0.01% to hit 0.8805.Also Thursday, the Confederation of British Industry said its retail sales balance fell at the fastest pace in over a year in July.In a separate report, U.K. building society Nationwide said its index of consumer confidence fell in July.             ]]></raw>
